snippet.textDisplay:
The chronology of "Ghostbusters Afterlife" is going to be weird. Canonicaly speaking, "Ghostbusters" took place in 1984 and 5 years later was "Ghostbusters 2" in 1989. Say Egon settled down in Jan 1990, had a family quickly, say his son was a honeymoon baby born in October 1990. Egon's son grows up and has kids of his own (Egon's grandchildren), a daughter who's 12(?) in this film and a son who looks about 14 in the film.

If "Ghostbusters Afterlife" takes place in 2019/2020 (30 years after last ghost sighting presumably 1989 in Ghostbusters 2) then the grandchildren would have to be born in 2005 and 2007. That means that Egon's son would've had his first kid at 15 and his second kid at 17, if not sooner?!

Was Egon a bad parent that lead to his son being a teen dad with a teen mom? Or maybe "Ghostbusters Afterlife" doesn't take place in 2019, maybe it takes place much later to accommodate said age issues. This really bothers me about the new movie. Other than that, this movie looks absolutely amazing!
